Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.98,0:00:06.15,comntry,,0,0,0,,WARNING: this commentary contains spoilers. Watch after completing the series.\NAlso, commentary tracks are not held to the same translation standard as regular dialogue tracks. This is a rough TL.\N{\1c&HADADAD&}The guest this time is the script writer:\N {\fnArial Unicode MS\fs50}虚淵玄{\fn\fs}(Urobuchi Gen).
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.31,0:00:06.98,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Okay! Well then, let's start, {\i1}Mahou Shoujo{\fnArial Unicode MS}☆{\fn}Madoka Magika{\i0} episode four commen—um,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.98,0:00:14.78,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,"{\i1}Miracles and Magic Do Exist{\i0}" commentary host, with the role of Madoka, I am Yuuki Aoi!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.78,0:00:10.53,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.86,0:00:13.40,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.78,0:00:18.28,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Yup, continuing, with the role of Akemi Homura, I'm Saitou Chiwa.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.28,0:00:19.16,chiwa,,0,0,0,,And this time—{\alpha&HFF&}this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.16,0:00:19.83,chiwa,,0,0,0,,And this time—{\1c&HB0B0FF&}this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.83,0:00:22.50,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Sorry for intruding. I'm the mastermind, Urobuchi Gen.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.50,0:00:24.67,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Yaaaay!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.50,0:00:23.54,chiwa,,0,0,0,,(lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.54,0:00:24.67,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Yaaaay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.67,0:00:26.54,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of things I want to say here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.54,0:00:29.46,chiwa,,0,0,0,,That's right, you certainly are the mastermind.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.04,0:00:28.00,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Nah, nah. How exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.46,0:00:30.67,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,That's right, truly.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.67,0:00:31.71,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.71,0:00:31.71,butch gen,,0,0,0,,No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.71,0:00:35.26,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Right! First off, this time it seems we'll have a small discussion about Kyousuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.26,0:00:36.01,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Ahhaha.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.26,0:00:36.01,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.01,0:00:36.97,chiwa,,0,0,0,,From Ao-chan:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.68,0:00:36.97,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Right—
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.97,0:00:44.19,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Actually, in episode two's commentary, I had specifically asked Ume-sensei about our beloved Kyousuke-kun's hair color...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.19,0:00:47.86,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,We had a conversation like "Is it white? Is it light brown?"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.86,0:00:56.28,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,But actually, the color that was in the version we used for commentary was something like a prototype, and um, what is it...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.28,0:01:00.33,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,When you see it on DVD, there isn't really a way it could be white,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.33,0:01:04.12,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,but there was a time when it was white, and then they added the light brown color later.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.12,0:01:05.29,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Right, it was a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.29,0:01:07.92,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Right! On the DVD it's light brown.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.87,0:01:07.92,butch gen,,0,0,0,,It was for internal use.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.92,0:01:08.50,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Right, right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.50,0:01:11.84,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,No, wait a second please, because when you see it in the volume, it was re-applied.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.84,0:01:16.22,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Right, so you might have felt like "Huh?", but... it's fixed!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.34,0:01:14.80,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ne?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.51,0:01:16.22,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,{\alpha&HFF&}Right, so you might have felt like "Huh?", but... {\alpha}it's fixed!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.22,0:01:19.01,chiwa,,0,0,0,,All traces have been completely removed!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.05,0:01:19.01,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,{\alpha&HFF&}All traces have been completely {\alpha}removed!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.01,0:01:19.85,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,After all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.26,0:01:19.85,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.85,0:01:23.98,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Now our uniforming of our good name is complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.81,0:01:21.39,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,{\alpha&HFF&}Now our {\alpha} uniforming!{\alpha&HFF&} of our good name is complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.72,0:01:22.27,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.43,0:01:23.98,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,{\alpha&HFF&}Now our uniforming of our good name is{\alpha} complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.98,0:01:26.98,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Now then, Urobuchi-san has come, what to do~?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.98,0:01:28.52,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,What to do~?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.52,0:01:30.44,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,What were you thinking when you wrote this story?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.44,0:01:31.86,chiwa,,0,0,0,,(lol) That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.86,0:01:33.86,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Ehh, so that's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.86,0:01:36.61,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Uhh, well... Right, as you might think...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.61,0:01:40.28,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Originally the basis was a {\i1}mahou shoujo{\i0} thing, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.28,0:01:45.62,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Well, that certainly isn't a genre that I've written for up until now, so it was odd to be entrusted with such a thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.62,0:01:48.37,chiwa,,0,0,0,,The starting point was SHAFT-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.37,0:01:52.71,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Right, um, Producer Iwakami-san had said, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.71,0:01:59.44,butch gen,,0,0,0,,"We're going back to {\i1}mahou shoujo{\i0}... Furthermore, it's with Shinbou-san and Ume-sensei."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.44,0:02:01.01,butch gen,,0,0,0,,"Well, we're being a bit deceitful, you know."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.01,0:02:04.02,butch gen,,0,0,0,,I was like "Just what the hell are you guys doing?" (lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.02,0:02:10.06,chiwa,,0,0,0,,At that time, were there any more bright choices, or was it already decided that this time a serious work will be made?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.06,0:02:15.36,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Well, right, pretty much from the start it was going to be serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.36,0:02:20.53,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah... well, yeah, this is commentary, so I can just be frank, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.99,0:02:20.53,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Yup, yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.53,0:02:25.45,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Well, in the very beginning, it was a {\i1}mahou shoujo{\i0}, and it was something like {\i1}Battle Royale{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.45,0:02:27.25,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Ehhhh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.45,0:02:27.25,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ahhh.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.12,0:02:27.25,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.25,0:02:30.25,butch gen,,0,0,0,,And, that would be, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.25,0:02:40.22,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Each and every time, starting after episode 1, a girl would die. Seems that would have been fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.84,0:02:36.80,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Ah, ahhh.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.80,0:02:40.22,chiwa,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.22,0:02:43.76,butch gen,,0,0,0,,"Nah, as you might think, every episode is a bit too cruel."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.76,0:02:46.27,butch gen,,0,0,0,,"Since we're doing it, let's just do from episode three or so."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.39,0:02:47.14,chiwa,,0,0,0,,(lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.27,0:02:47.48,butch gen,,0,0,0,,There was that conversation. (lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.48,0:02:49.14,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,In its own way, that's even more cruel...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.48,0:02:49.14,butch gen,,0,0,0,,(lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.14,0:02:54.82,chiwa,,0,0,0,,That's right, it kind of leaves a huge impression on you when there's that gap.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.82,0:02:57.07,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Well, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.07,0:02:58.61,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Well, that was the intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.44,0:02:58.61,chiwa,,0,0,0,,And the number of characters, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.61,0:02:59.20,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.20,0:03:03.07,chiwa,,0,0,0,,About how many characters did you want to have?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.78,0:03:03.07,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Ah, I lent a hand in figuring that out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.07,0:03:03.91,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Ahhh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.53,0:03:03.91,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.91,0:03:07.25,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Well, twelve episodes was decided from the onset, after all. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.41,0:03:06.54,chiwa,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.75,0:03:13.29,butch gen,,0,0,0,,If we had more characters than this, we wouldn't be able to properly "biograph" them. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.33,0:03:13.29,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Ohhh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.92,0:03:13.29,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.29,0:03:15.71,chiwa,,0,0,0,,I see... Really, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.71,0:03:17.71,chiwa,,0,0,0,,There are really so many things I want to ask!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.71,0:03:19.38,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Since I have the chance, I'd like to ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.38,0:03:26.01,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Urobuchi-san, you were at the auditions, so I'd like to hear a little bit about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.22,0:03:22.34,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes, yeah. I was there. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.47,0:03:26.22,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.01,0:03:32.81,chiwa,,0,0,0,,I mentioned this once before certainly, but Ao-chan and I had coincidentally run into each other at auditions...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.73,0:03:32.19,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,We were together coincidentally!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.81,0:03:39.28,chiwa,,0,0,0,,There were so many girls that seemed younger than Ao-chan, and then I was there...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.86,0:03:39.90,butch gen,,0,0,0,,AHhahahaha.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.90,0:03:37.02,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.28,0:03:43.99,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Then, you know, the fact there were so many characters was another amazing part.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.99,0:03:45.24,butch gen,,0,0,0,,(lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.24,0:03:48.95,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Thanks to you, there are a lot. So then, what is it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.95,0:03:54.71,chiwa,,0,0,0,,The auditions were held while allowing us to pick a character we'd like, and such...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.41,0:03:53.37,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,That's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.00,0:03:52.75,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.71,0:03:58.30,butch gen,,0,0,0,,That's right, um... that's a considerably rare style, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.13,0:03:55.79,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.30,0:04:00.47,chiwa,,0,0,0,,It's very rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.05,0:04:00.47,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Mm!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.09,0:04:00.47,butch gen,,0,0,0,,AHhaha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.47,0:04:03.84,butch gen,,0,0,0,,This is the first time I've overseen such a thing, personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.84,0:04:07.64,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I usually see them on tapes and such. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.64,0:04:11.06,butch gen,,0,0,0,,"Ah I see, I can't decide on a tone of voice that I like." Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.06,0:04:20.19,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Urobuchi-san, you were really the one who said, "Please try Homura," to me when I was doing a different role.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.48,0:04:18.07,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Ah, um, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.07,0:04:20.19,butch gen,,0,0,0,,That's right. Yeah. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.19,0:04:24.74,butch gen,,0,0,0,,You really have that, what is it, "dark beauty" feeling. (lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.74,0:04:25.24,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ahh!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.24,0:04:26.66,butch gen,,0,0,0,,So I requested that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.66,0:04:30.20,chiwa,,0,0,0,,During the audition phase, did you already know the entire scenario?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.20,0:04:31.08,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Ah, that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.08,0:04:32.08,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes. That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.08,0:04:34.87,butch gen,,0,0,0,,To be frank, I was the only one who knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.08,0:04:34.87,chiwa,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.87,0:04:38.09,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Even if there weren't details, you knew about things such as episode 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.09,0:04:40.09,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Well, that was there too. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.09,0:04:41.88,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,{\fnArial Unicode MS}تشان، الثابتة والمتنقلة نقاش{\fn}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.88,0:04:46.30,chiwa,,0,0,0,,How did Madoka go? Actually, I believe she's the hardest character.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.88,0:04:46.30,butch gen,,0,0,0,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.30,0:04:51.10,butch gen,,0,0,0,,We asked everyone to feel a bit hazy and gloomy. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.10,0:04:55.19,butch gen,,0,0,0,,In the end, really, um... right,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.19,0:04:59.07,butch gen,,0,0,0,,we thought you were the most "unadulterated" if you will.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.07,0:05:00.57,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ahhhh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.57,0:05:00.57,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Ahhhh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.94,0:05:00.57,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.57,0:05:11.29,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Umm... you possessed something like a cute girl, that worked in pleasant way and felt like a girly protagonist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.29,0:05:14.25,butch gen,,0,0,0,,It didn't come off like you were forcing an act.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.25,0:05:18.04,butch gen,,0,0,0,,What is it, umm... well, see,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.04,0:05:19.54,butch gen,,0,0,0,,umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.54,0:05:24.42,butch gen,,0,0,0,,That scene where she has a conversation with Kyubey by her bedside,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.05,0:05:22.92,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.42,0:05:30.97,butch gen,,0,0,0,,to an extent, while it isn't bad, she gives you an impression of being half asleep, or like...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.97,0:05:33.64,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Umm, it feels a bit like a natural airhead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.64,0:05:39.15,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Umm, it gives off an air like "This is nice." Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.60,0:05:35.31,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ohhh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.35,0:05:39.06,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ahhhh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.15,0:05:43.11,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Umm... What is it... umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.36,0:05:41.61,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,{\fs30\bord1.5}thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.11,0:05:45.32,butch gen,,0,0,0,,It's like an "absent-minded" feeling. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.99,0:05:45.32,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,(lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.32,0:05:46.20,chiwa,,0,0,0,,(lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.20,0:05:47.45,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Feel like can't converse!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.45,0:05:54.50,butch gen,,0,0,0,,"With no boys [in the cast], there will be conversations like this." I like that feeling. It's nice, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.50,0:05:55.87,chiwa,,0,0,0,,I get it, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.87,0:06:02.13,chiwa,,0,0,0,,She might be the most difficult character, and she runs away from her situations a lot, like she isn't sure where to go,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.13,0:06:03.92,chiwa,,0,0,0,,but, she's a good girl, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.92,0:06:04.38,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.38,0:06:08.40,chiwa,,0,0,0,,But, it's different from the good girls you'd usually see in anime.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.96,0:06:05.13,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,mmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.93,0:06:08.59,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,mmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.40,0:06:11.36,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Really, she's the type of girl who, if she was real,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.36,0:06:14.40,chiwa,,0,0,0,,everyone would say "She's such a good girl, isn't she?"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.40,0:06:17.94,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,If you look closely, I think the real person is a good girl, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.94,0:06:21.48,chiwa,,0,0,0,,She tries her best, huh? In the real world too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.94,0:06:18.94,butch gen,,0,0,0,,(lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.85,0:06:20.90,butch gen,,0,0,0,,That's right, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.48,0:06:28.03,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Right. Actually, before this, we had this conversation with Mizuhashi Kaori-san in episode 3's commentary, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.03,0:06:33.91,chiwa,,0,0,0,,When we were talking about characters, it was said that girls' and guys' viewpoints change a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.58,0:06:33.91,butch gen,,0,0,0,,AHhahaha.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.82,0:06:33.20,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.91,0:06:35.94,chiwa,,0,0,0,,We had that conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.94,0:06:40.67,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Well, when you look at the story as a whole, it really changes with each individual person, so I didn't get into that,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.67,0:06:45.21,chiwa,,0,0,0,,but we were talking about how the characters give off different impressions between men and women.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.21,0:06:47.26,chiwa,,0,0,0,,But Urobuchi-san is a guy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.26,0:06:47.26,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,{\alpha&HFF&}But Urobuchi-san {\alpha}is a guy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.26,0:06:49.51,chiwa,,0,0,0,,So, why do you understand that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.59,0:06:49.51,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,{\alpha&HFF&}So, why do you{\alpha} understand that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.51,0:06:51.09,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Nah, that's–
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.18,0:06:51.09,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,You're a girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.09,0:06:53.60,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Ehhhh, reallyyyy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.76,0:06:53.05,chiwa,,0,0,0,,You're really a girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.60,0:06:57.89,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Well, nah, what to say... If I didn't understand that, I couldn't work, you know (lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.89,0:06:59.35,butch gen,,0,0,0,,In these icy waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.35,0:07:01.73,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,So are you constantly observing humans?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.73,0:07:05.69,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Well, right... Well, that's something to take into concern, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.69,0:07:06.94,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,He can see through...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.94,0:07:08.95,chiwa,,0,0,0,,He can see through us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.86,0:07:08.95,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,I was had!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.95,0:07:10.99,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.90,0:07:10.99,butch gen,,0,0,0,,No, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.99,0:07:15.16,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Well, when we first heard that discussion, we thought "{\i1}Hee{\i0}~?"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.16,0:07:18.29,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Kaori-san, too, thought "Ah, that might be true~"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.29,0:07:20.64,chiwa,,0,0,0,,But, guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.64,0:07:29.34,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Well, since we consisted of nothing but women in the booth, we had no second opinions, but do you think the viewpoints differ?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.47,0:07:34.30,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Right, well, really, umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.30,0:07:39.31,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Ahh, well certainly, as for what was paid attention to this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.31,0:07:44.27,butch gen,,0,0,0,,This wasn't really made with appeal to guys in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.27,0:07:46.02,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Ahhh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.56,0:07:46.02,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Mmmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.02,0:07:52.45,butch gen,,0,0,0,,If you were a boy watching, you would simply want to see nothing but pretty girls talking, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.45,0:07:55.83,chiwa,,0,0,0,,From a girl's perspective, it's really like "Ahhhh!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.41,0:07:55.83,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.83,0:07:58.70,butch gen,,0,0,0,,No, this connects with the audition conversation from before, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.70,0:08:06.04,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Really, for the person you call a "protagonist," everyone stays aware of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.04,0:08:09.76,butch gen,,0,0,0,,For example, when there is a scene where she's alone in her own room...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.76,0:08:11.84,butch gen,,0,0,0,,From a male's viewpoint, what he'd feel is the acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.84,0:08:16.30,butch gen,,0,0,0,,You know, that's natural, since the male viewers are watching something "distant" on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.30,0:08:19.35,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Um... we went without that feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.85,0:08:20.85,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.35,0:08:22.60,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,I see, I get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.60,0:08:28.52,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Unintentionally, even for scenes that are acted out by a single person, cute acting will come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.52,0:08:29.94,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.94,0:08:39.29,butch gen,,0,0,0,,So it's very much like, when there's a girl alone in a room... what kind of acting will there be, or what kind of words will be spoken?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.29,0:08:43.96,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ahhh, you were able to see such a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.66,0:08:43.96,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Ne~
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.96,0:08:49.38,chiwa,,0,0,0,,A part that was very much on my mind regarding the situation of the characters: Well, they're really cute, very natural as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.38,0:08:54.47,chiwa,,0,0,0,,which is especially true since they're children. I find their childish qualities extremely cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.47,0:08:58.10,chiwa,,0,0,0,,But even if you don't keep in mind that they're children, it's cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.26,0:08:58.10,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.10,0:09:01.97,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Still, they've got a relatively "cute, cute!" childish presentation to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.97,0:09:06.42,chiwa,,0,0,0,,This scene where Madoka is crying is true for that too, a very cute crying presentation...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.42,0:09:09.90,chiwa,,0,0,0,,From the viewpoint of an actor, that's one part of drama,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.90,0:09:14.11,chiwa,,0,0,0,,but that's different from the true meaning of the tears—sadness and hardship.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.11,0:09:14.99,chiwa,,0,0,0,,{\fs45}Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.99,0:09:15.86,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,{\fs45}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.86,0:09:18.41,chiwa,,0,0,0,,{\fs45}That's right... Homura has come.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.66,0:09:18.41,butch gen,,0,0,0,,{\fs45}Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.41,0:09:20.99,chiwa,,0,0,0,,I really love conversation scenes between these two!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.99,0:09:22.08,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Uwaah~
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.45,0:09:24.41,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Somehow, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.41,0:09:27.33,chiwa,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mou{\i0}... I really feel that way, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.33,0:09:27.96,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ne~
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.96,0:09:29.46,chiwa,,0,0,0,,There's a reason, isn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.46,0:09:31.88,butch gen,,0,0,0,,S–She's finally speaking kind words.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.88,0:09:32.88,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.88,0:09:32.88,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,That's right, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.88,0:09:34.72,butch gen,,0,0,0,,She's always been {\i1}tsun{\i0} up until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.72,0:09:36.68,chiwa,,0,0,0,,All the way until the end of episode 3, she tried REALLY hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.68,0:09:37.30,butch gen,,0,0,0,,(lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.30,0:09:41.18,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Homura tried hard to be {\i1}tsundere{\i0}! Or well, {\i1}tsun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.18,0:09:43.02,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,She stayed cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.02,0:09:44.98,butch gen,,0,0,0,,In order to understand all of that, you have to watch episode ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.98,0:09:47.27,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It hasn't come yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.98,0:09:47.27,chiwa,,0,0,0,,But actually in episode four...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.27,0:09:47.77,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.77,0:09:50.23,chiwa,,0,0,0,,There's a part to be a bit aware of...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.15,0:09:50.23,butch gen,,0,0,0,,AHhahaha.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.23,0:09:51.19,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.23,0:09:51.19,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ahh.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.19,0:09:53.36,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Well, that's right. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.36,0:09:55.57,chiwa,,0,0,0,,The lines a little bit after this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.57,0:09:55.99,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.99,0:09:56.45,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Somehow...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.45,0:10:01.03,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,This is another part that really hurts to act!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.03,0:10:02.41,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Like right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.41,0:10:03.16,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.16,0:10:08.87,chiwa,,0,0,0,,I felt very mindful of this, and I thought it was a display of her kindness...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.87,0:10:15.67,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Now and then—I suppose that after episode three, she becomes a little {\i1}dere{\i0} here and there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.67,0:10:23.60,chiwa,,0,0,0,,The air around Homura is completely different when she's alone with Madoka, compared to when other characters are with them...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.60,0:10:23.60,butch gen,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.60,0:10:25.31,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,It's like the guard she puts up is much different.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.31,0:10:26.77,chiwa,,0,0,0,,That's right, right now she's a bit more soft.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.77,0:10:29.85,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ne? You have the ability to soften or harden a girl, Madoka.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.85,0:10:31.27,chiwa,,0,0,0,,(lol) Right, right, right
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.27,0:10:32.77,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Like "This time too, I'll soften you up!"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.77,0:10:33.77,chiwa,,0,0,0,,(lol) Right, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.77,0:10:37.57,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Then if Sayaka-chan is like "Hey!", she'll be like "Tsk."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.48,0:10:35.86,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,{\alpha&HFF&}Then if Sayaka-chan is like "Hey!", she'll be like {\alpha}"Tsk."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.57,0:10:39.57,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,She'll get mad and go "Ahhhh!"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.57,0:10:42.95,butch gen,,0,0,0,,This is kind of like her "Desperate" guard-style, isn't it? This commonly talking Homura.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.95,0:10:49.08,chiwa,,0,0,0,,She's so tender, isn't she? Really, I can't say it! She's so patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.08,0:10:53.75,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,But you know, for the Madoka who won't go as far as completely accepting that, she isn't just being kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.75,0:11:00.30,chiwa,,0,0,0,,But that's very realistic, isn't it? Usually, the protagonist would get tougher and take on everything by now...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.30,0:11:05.35,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Taking on Homura's pain too, but Madoka hasn't taken on anything yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.43,0:11:05.35,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Well, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.35,0:11:07.18,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,She hasn't saved anyone yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.47,0:11:07.18,butch gen,,0,0,0,,(lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.18,0:11:08.60,chiwa,,0,0,0,,No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.60,0:11:12.40,chiwa,,0,0,0,,But because of that, I believe that everyone feels like they're in the center [of the story].
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.40,0:11:14.15,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ahhh!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.15,0:11:21.61,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,But, what it is it, it feels like she carries the most sympathy for other girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.24,0:11:20.36,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Ah, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.61,0:11:26.34,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,When I took the auditions and was told to do the most sympathetic Madoka,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.34,0:11:29.66,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,I thought, "Ah, this person is shaken up. She's very close to me."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.71,0:11:34.67,chiwa,,0,0,0,,You know, all the characters fit themselves in reality, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.67,0:11:35.75,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,That's right, actually!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.84,0:11:35.75,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Ahhh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.75,0:11:37.38,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Is that how it is? I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.38,0:11:41.22,chiwa,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mou{\i0}, Kitamura Eri doing Miki Sayaka is just perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.01,0:11:41.22,butch gen,,0,0,0,,(lol) Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.22,0:11:43.64,chiwa,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mou{\i0}, it's truly perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.93,0:11:42.80,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Uwaa!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.18,0:11:44.35,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Uwaah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.64,0:11:46.31,chiwa,,0,0,0,,She's really a good girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.35,0:11:46.31,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.31,0:11:55.19,chiwa,,0,0,0,,But then, she has that cheerful, joking feeling to her... and then more than anyone else, she's uneasy... she's such a nice girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.14,0:11:48.18,butch gen,,0,0,0,,{\fs45}Uwaah
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.27,0:11:54.56,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Uwaaaah~
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.19,0:11:56.27,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Saying that now... (lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.27,0:11:57.69,chiwa,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.27,0:11:57.69,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.69,0:11:59.65,chiwa,,0,0,0,,You'd say it's rather unexpected, though, ne?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.65,0:12:02.11,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Right, like it just happened right before your eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.11,0:12:04.32,butch gen,,0,0,0,,I wrote that story, but it's still hard to watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.32,0:12:05.49,chiwa,,0,0,0,,(lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.78,0:12:05.49,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.58,0:12:08.62,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yaaaa...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.58,0:12:08.62,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Really...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.62,0:12:09.79,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.79,0:12:17.21,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Really, somehow, when I tried Homura out, my heart was going "de-de-de-de-de-de, de-de-de-de!"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.67,0:12:14.96,butch gen,,0,0,0,,(lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.46,0:12:29.72,notes,,0,0,0,,Zoku{\fnArial Unicode MS}・{\fn}Satsuriku no Django -Jigoku no Shoukinkubi- (2007)\NA nitroplus game featuring a fully female cast written by Urobuchi Gen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.46,0:12:23.38,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Well, this is the first time I've wrote anything so full of girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.38,0:12:24.55,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.55,0:12:28.51,butch gen,,0,0,0,,In the past, all the stories I've written have had guys in higher positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.51,0:12:29.72,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.72,0:12:33.02,butch gen,,0,0,0,,But this time it's basically just Kyousuke and the father, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.02,0:12:36.11,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Right, and the little brother. Then, Beh-san! Where's Beh-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.11,0:12:36.86,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Hang on, Beh-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.86,0:12:38.86,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Where is Beh-san's position?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.86,0:12:41.07,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Beh-san doesn't have a gender, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.07,0:12:43.24,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ah, so that's it? It's like a gender-bending QB.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.24,0:12:46.74,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Yeah, if Urobuchi-san says it, I believe it has to be the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.03,0:12:46.32,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.74,0:12:49.62,chiwa,,0,0,0,,In many different places, many different staff-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.62,0:12:56.42,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Whether or not Urobuchi-san regards QB to be a male animal has probably bugged people in various interviews and such.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.42,0:12:58.04,chiwa,,0,0,0,,It has bugged us as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.04,0:12:58.04,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,{\alpha&HFF&}It has  {\alpha}bugged us!{\alpha&HFF&} as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.04,0:13:01.17,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess I haven't said it too many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.17,0:13:01.17,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,{\alpha&HFF&}Well, I guess I haven't s s{\alpha}(lol) too many{\alpha&HFF&} times.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.17,0:13:02.42,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Not too many!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.17,0:13:02.42,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yaaa...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.42,0:13:07.68,emirin,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnArial Unicode MS\fs50}わけがわからないよ{\fs45\fn}(wake ga wakaranai yo) - I don't get the reason.\NThis is a line QB says in ep6. It's become a pretty famous line.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.42,0:13:03.30,emirin,,0,0,0,,I don't get the reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.30,0:13:04.43,chiwa,,0,0,0,,(lol) {\alpha&HFF&}Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.30,0:13:04.93,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,(lol) {\alpha&HFF&}Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.43,0:13:04.93,chiwa,,0,0,0,,(lol) Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.93,0:13:06.34,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,There it is!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.51,0:13:06.34,chiwa,,0,0,0,,There it is.{\alpha&HFF&}!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.34,0:13:07.39,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,There it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.39,0:13:12.60,chiwa,,0,0,0,,But if you look at the most calm one, QB is the one who's never shaken up at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.60,0:13:15.02,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Well, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.39,0:13:15.02,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.02,0:13:18.15,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,He certainly says some righteous things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.56,0:13:18.15,chiwa,,0,0,0,,That's right, right right right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.15,0:13:18.77,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Mm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.77,0:13:24.65,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Well you know, more than anyone else, he's thinking in the long term.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.15,0:13:24.65,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,That's right, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.65,0:13:28.99,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,When you think about the continuance of everything, really, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.24,0:13:28.99,butch gen,,0,0,0,,mm...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.99,0:13:30.08,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,ahhhh.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.08,0:13:36.46,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Right, rather than thinking about the happiness of himself or someone that he likes, it's much bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.46,0:13:40.09,chiwa,,0,0,0,,QB is talking about something closer to the scale of world peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.09,0:13:42.34,chiwa,,0,0,0,,It's kind of like... "What to do?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.34,0:13:43.76,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Right? I see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.76,0:13:49.01,butch gen,,0,0,0,,No, but in the first place humans aren't righteous, so you can think of him of as a wonderful animal.{「そもそも人ってのは正しくないから素晴らしい生き物だろうって思うのもあるんで」←同意 }
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.01,0:13:58.48,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Since he's purely righteous and just, he's an animal that doesn't need people or love.{QBさんは正しいだけの存在だから人とあい入れない部分もあるのかもねえという話。}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.48,0:13:59.61,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.61,0:14:06.86,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Amazing, you know. Why is it so... I believe each character has their very own situations...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.86,0:14:14.20,chiwa,,0,0,0,,It's like there's no way this was written by one person. Who's in your head? Where are you looking from, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.24,0:14:13.04,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,How many people are up there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.20,0:14:24.25,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Ahh, well, that's right... Umm, you could say that in that regard, a writer, and the acting that plays out that writing, are different.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.25,0:14:31.10,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Really, this is my first time writing while commanding a view of so many different characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.10,0:14:37.06,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Actually, when I focused myself in on writing a single character intently,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.06,0:14:42.86,butch gen,,0,0,0,,all the way until the core, there were many parts that I thought would need to be given an awesome performance. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.86,0:14:46.28,butch gen,,0,0,0,,There are parts where it was like "Oh, I didn't think so far into it."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.28,0:14:52.70,butch gen,,0,0,0,,When polishing them up to be performed, it was like "Ah, we don't really need this line."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.70,0:14:54.70,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Ehhh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.08,0:14:54.70,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ehhh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.70,0:15:01.96,butch gen,,0,0,0,,If you want to have this sort of feeling, then you don't need to use a lot of words to explain many of the scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.96,0:15:02.71,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.71,0:15:04.32,chiwa,,0,0,0,,But this piece of work has a few things that are like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.32,0:15:06.46,butch gen,,0,0,0,,It has them, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.21,0:15:06.46,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Ohhh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.46,0:15:12.55,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Well, like, earlier, regarding Madoka's mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.47,0:15:06.98,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Like where?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.93,0:15:12.55,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Ah, ahhh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.93,0:15:12.55,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,{\alpha&HFF&}Ah, {\alpha}ahhh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.55,0:15:14.56,butch gen,,0,0,0,,She's scary enough, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.18,0:15:14.56,chiwa,,0,0,0,,(lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.56,0:15:18.98,butch gen,,0,0,0,,If she didn't say "Mama, you have scary eyes" then it'd have just been "Mama, you're scary."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.43,0:15:18.98,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,(lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.98,0:15:21.48,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Mama is scary. (lol) That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.15,0:15:27.40,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Well for that, if it wasn't said, an assumption regarding that may have not been formed at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.40,0:15:31.32,butch gen,,0,0,0,,So really, "Your eyes are scary" should be written. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.32,0:15:46.63,notes,,0,0,0,,For those who aren't aware, Urobuchi Gen-san normally writes text/narration heavy game scripts or light novels, which may be a part of why the relatively thin writing style suited for an anime may have slipped his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.32,0:15:36.03,butch gen,,0,0,0,,That sort of minimal explanation style is something I'm not well acquainted with.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.83,0:15:36.03,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.03,0:15:42.25,butch gen,,0,0,0,,But regarding that point, for something that starts out as anime, if you say something too much...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.25,0:15:45.50,butch gen,,0,0,0,,You could say it'd be too much explanation through their lines. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.50,0:15:52.13,butch gen,,0,0,0,,If you keep firmly planting lines, it'll make people think "Ah, they're still saying that..."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.75,0:15:46.88,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,It's difficult, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.13,0:15:55.01,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ehhh, I never once thought that! (lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.01,0:15:56.26,butch gen,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yaa{\i0}, really...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.26,0:16:02.14,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Regarding that, it's really something you could say there was guidance on... or you could say it's something everyone created.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.14,0:16:09.74,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Before this, I had really developed a habit of not putting any weight on {\i1}seiyuu{\i0} when writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.74,0:16:10.57,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.57,0:16:19.08,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Are there any characters whose impression changed a lot when everyone began acting them out?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.08,0:16:27.13,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Right, really... Mami-san was quite... yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.13,0:16:33.09,butch gen,,0,0,0,,I didn't think she'd become such a fleshed-out character after only 3 episodes. Yeah.{マミは、たった3話であそこまでのキャラになるとは思わなかった。}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.59,0:16:47.02,butch gen,,0,0,0,,That's right, ne... it was a bit like she had more of an impact on the distance of those other two, and it gave it a lot more meaning later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.02,0:16:56.57,mizuhasu,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs40}To Mizuhashi Kaori-san: GJ.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.02,0:16:56.57,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Compared to when I wrote it myself, the sense of loss went way beyond my expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.57,0:17:03.25,chiwa,,0,0,0,,And after that, Madoka and Sayaka's relationship was getting pulled apart by Mami-san's existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.25,0:17:11.00,butch gen,,0,0,0,,That's something I believe was a really straightforward setup.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.00,0:17:18.14,chiwa,,0,0,0,,When doing this piece of work, the thoughts for us who are actors, doing things inside of a booth... It's really like...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.14,0:17:22.18,chiwa,,0,0,0,,So far, everything has been... Extremely interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.18,0:17:23.73,chiwa,,0,0,0,,I'd say.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.18,0:17:23.73,butch gen,,0,0,0,,(lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.18,0:17:23.73,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ne~
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.73,0:17:30.32,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Well, for other pieces of work, of course there's a lot to get involved in, and lots of people...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.32,0:17:37.45,chiwa,,0,0,0,,But this time, it's like everyone really carved or engraved themselves into this. (lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.45,0:17:45.33,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Somehow, it's really like... everyone had a lot of trust placed in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.33,0:17:48.58,chiwa,,0,0,0,,I feel like it was very worth doing...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.58,0:17:52.59,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Then, I think it leaves a staggeringly large impression on your consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.59,0:17:58.14,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Somehow, if I'm not in the company of people I can completely trust...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.14,0:18:01.26,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,I'm not able to do this kind of "I can put anything out there" acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.26,0:18:02.72,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,It's really scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.72,0:18:03.64,butch gen,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.64,0:18:09.10,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,And then they have to see the entire vocabulary within you, including things you don't want them to...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.10,0:18:09.65,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.65,0:18:18.24,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,When I watch this kind of "I can't run away from here" part, I definitely couldn't do this without these kind of members.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.24,0:18:25.95,chiwa,,0,0,0,,That's right. And it's true for the staff-san as well, this is my first time working with Urobuchi-san, but for SHAFT-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.95,0:18:37.72,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Somehow, the people are very familiar, and for the actors as well, no one was like "Hello, nice to meet you,"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.72,0:18:45.06,chiwa,,0,0,0,,it's like we didn't start from zero... Well, this piece of work probably began at stage zero...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.06,0:18:51.48,chiwa,,0,0,0,,But in terms of trustworthy relationships, we've started together around 5 or 6 times now, and things have steadily increased.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.48,0:18:54.40,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Somehow, I feel extremely grateful for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.40,0:18:58.07,butch gen,,0,0,0,,For you to say that makes me extremely happy, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.07,0:19:03.72,chiwa,,0,0,0,,And then it was like, "After coming this far, there's no way things won't be fun!"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.72,0:19:06.83,chiwa,,0,0,0,,It's always like "What'll happen next week, what'll happen next week?"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.83,0:19:08.58,chiwa,,0,0,0,,"Why don't we get to see the full script?"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.12,0:19:10.00,butch gen,,0,0,0,,(lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.58,0:19:10.00,chiwa,,0,0,0,,(lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.00,0:19:12.08,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Like "Why do we get the script on the same day we have to act?"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.00,0:19:12.08,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Well, well, that's a bit of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.08,0:19:12.58,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.58,0:19:15.50,chiwa,,0,0,0,,That sort of thing is really how the feeling is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.71,0:19:15.50,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Right. This much you really want to push through.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.50,0:19:17.51,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Like "I WANT TO KNOW THIS!"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.51,0:19:24.05,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,But it's like intense polishing of the script, up until the very last moments.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.84,0:19:24.05,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Right, right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.05,0:19:25.51,chiwa,,0,0,0,,And because of that, it is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.51,0:19:25.76,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ne?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.76,0:19:29.23,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Then for one week, you're thinking about things, which steadily increased the impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.23,0:19:29.94,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.94,0:19:35.23,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Because of that it had more impact in the end, I feel like one week is around the perfect amount [of time].
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.23,0:19:40.20,butch gen,,0,0,0,,It certainly pulls you in when you put thought into it. Yeah. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.20,0:19:45.66,chiwa,,0,0,0,,And since everyone is trustworthy, as soon as we start fixing things, we can instantly make corrections.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.66,0:19:46.91,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Mm, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.91,0:19:51.00,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Ah, this is Inu Curry-san's directing here...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.04,0:19:52.37,butch gen,,0,0,0,,This is another amazing thing, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.37,0:19:55.88,butch gen,,0,0,0,,You know, these never were present once in the scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.88,0:19:57.00,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Ah, what was it like?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.00,0:20:01.05,butch gen,,0,0,0,,No, really, it was many lines. There was a bit of line revision.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.05,0:20:11.02,butch gen,,0,0,0,,And after these lines, they jumped in. Inu Curry-san made everything related to the barriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.02,0:20:15.52,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Like the part with Madoka being pulled or getting killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.48,0:20:14.77,butch gen,,0,0,0,,(lol)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.52,0:20:26.74,butch gen,,0,0,0,,For that area, right, you could say it's completely an original from the minds of Inu Curry-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.74,0:20:28.12,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.12,0:20:32.50,butch gen,,0,0,0,,During the script-writing stages, monster designs weren't made.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.50,0:20:35.79,butch gen,,0,0,0,,And it wasn't clear exactly what kind of action there would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.79,0:20:38.75,butch gen,,0,0,0,,So there were no lines or anything for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.75,0:20:40.38,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.38,0:20:47.89,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Right, somehow since the script's stage directing was torn apart and scattered around to different people's presentations,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.89,0:20:50.18,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,I really think, "It can be done,"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.18,0:20:54.35,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Then it's like, "GROW!" That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.35,0:20:55.98,butch gen,,0,0,0,,It'd be called "going beyond your imagination," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.98,0:20:58.90,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Right, I think going beyond your imagination is scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.90,0:21:02.57,chiwa,,0,0,0,,That's right, really, you know~
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.57,0:21:05.82,chiwa,,0,0,0,,I see, so things were really entrusted to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.82,0:21:10.20,butch gen,,0,0,0,,That's right, really, that's... Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.74,0:21:08.12,chiwa,,0,0,0,,That was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.20,0:21:14.83,butch gen,,0,0,0,,I haven't written many stories like this before, yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.83,0:21:19.46,butch gen,,0,0,0,,For that point, really, what words should be spoken or what kind of air should be held...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.46,0:21:23.26,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Right, you could say I would have needed a bit of help from the onset.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.26,0:21:30.22,butch gen,,0,0,0,,And after that, there's the topic of relying on actors.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.31,0:21:35.06,chiwa,,0,0,0,,But somehow with that, it's just become better.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.06,0:21:37.31,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,It's got amazing endurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.31,0:21:46.57,butch gen,,0,0,0,,That's right, really... there are parts that I just couldn't have made by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.57,0:21:48.03,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Here's the new character!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.03,0:21:49.57,chiwa,,0,0,0,,I love her~
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.57,0:21:51.58,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,{\fnArial Unicode MS}♥{\fn} I love her{\fnArial Unicode MS}～♥
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.41,0:21:51.58,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Kyouko-tan~
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.58,0:21:52.49,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,She's the best!{\fnArial Unicode MS}♥
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.49,0:21:54.29,butch gen,,0,0,0,,This is a scene I like, myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.29,0:21:55.91,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's right, isn't it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.91,0:21:57.87,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,{\fs45}I see... {\fs}Cute—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.87,0:22:00.50,chiwa,,0,0,0,,A new character has finally come.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.33,0:22:00.50,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.50,0:22:02.63,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,She was in the opening, and here she is for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.63,0:22:05.17,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,It's like "Who's that rival girl? Who is she?"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.17,0:22:06.05,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,*giggle*{sorry it was just too cute}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.05,0:22:13.52,butch gen,,0,0,0,,You know, Ume-sensei has never really made any characters that have her sort of "bad-style" before.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.52,0:22:17.56,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Right, and then Ai-chan's play of her is super cute, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.52,0:22:16.06,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Ne~!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.52,0:22:17.56,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.52,0:22:17.56,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.56,0:22:19.48,chiwa,,0,0,0,,That unbalance is unbearable!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.02,0:22:20.11,butch gen,,0,0,0,,That's right, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.48,0:22:20.27,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,Unbearable!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.27,0:22:21.82,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.82,0:22:24.32,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,I feel like this is another girl's "something"!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.32,0:22:30.57,butch gen,,0,0,0,,That's an original part, too, and I feel like the bad-girl acting was pleasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.57,0:22:31.62,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.62,0:22:39.50,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Well, I think that's great. And it's a bit unpredictable, too, according to Shinbou-san's guidance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.50,0:22:40.79,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.34,0:22:44.63,chiwa,,0,0,0,,I see, from now on, Kyouko will be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.63,0:22:46.88,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,That's right, it'll be exciting, won't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.88,0:22:48.30,chiwa,,0,0,0,,It gets so amazing from here!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.30,0:22:51.34,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,There are so many things I want to ask, why are we so close to ending?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.34,0:22:57.02,chiwa,,0,0,0,,To be honest, in this phase we know a lot, but we don't know the finale.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.02,0:23:00.02,chiwa,,0,0,0,,We haven't done after recording for episode twelve yet, and we haven't read the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.02,0:22:58.10,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.02,0:22:57.64,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.02,0:23:00.56,ao-chan,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.56,0:23:04.65,chiwa,,0,0,0,,So there's no choice but to ask Urobuchi-san, {\i1}what's going to happen!?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.65,0:23:09.65,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Umm, right, well without spoilers I can't really say too much, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.28,0:23:08.86,chiwa,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.65,0:23:17.00,butch gen,,0,0,0,,Umm... regarding the ending, it wasn't to be in complete despair.
